<article>
    <h1>SALT THER&#xAD;APY FA&#xAD;CIALS AT PABLO BLAU</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201225/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-25"><time>2020-12-25</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE STYLE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Fancy a lux­ury treat­ment in a cave of salt? For an un­usual up­grade to your usual fa­cial, lo­cal spa Pablo Blau might be worth a trip.</p>
    <p>The spa, which opened in Oc­to­ber last year, of­fers treat­ments in a salt room en­vi­ron­ment said to mimic salt mines and caves in Eastern Europe. Salt ther­apy or halother­apy, though lesser-known here, dates back to the 12th cen­tury and banks on ur­ban myths of salt min­ers in Poland emerg­ing with younger and clearer skin.</p>
    <p>Other sup­posed ben­e­fits of in­hal­ing fine salt par­ti­cles in­clude im­proved res­pi­ra­tory and al­lergy is­sues, im­proved blood cir­cu­la­tion and bet­ter sleep. Halother­apy is an un­proven treat­ment, but favoured within the well­ness in­dus­try.</p>
    <p>Con­trary to what it may sound like, salt ther­apy has noth­ing to do with rub­bing salt into the skin.</p>
    <p>At Pablo Blau, fa­cial treat­ments take place in rooms coated with phar­ma­ceu­ti­cal-grade dry salt crys­tals.</p>
    <p>A salt gen­er­a­tor grinds and pro­duces at­mo­spheric salt par­ti­cles that fill the air – th­ese are said to clear con­ges­tion and calm in­flam­ma­tion.</p>
    <p>Fa­cials range from anti-age­ing to pu­ri­fy­ing treat­ments, and the spa of­fers eye, neck and body treat­ments as well. A 60-minute Sig­na­ture Salt Room Cus­tomised Fa­cial tai­lored to your skin costs up to $390.</p>
    <p>For those hun­gry for travel, 90 min­utes in the sig­na­ture salt rooms can feel like a brief, but ful­fill­ing es­cape to another land. Info: 02-26A, Raf­fles City Shop­ping Cen­tre, 252 North</p>
    <p>Bridge Road. To book, call 6261-6885 or go to pabloblau.com</p>

